data.name: Beef and Vegetable Stew with Rice
data.quickTastyDescription: A hearty and comforting beef stew packed with vegetables, served over fluffy rice.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large pot, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the chopped onion and garlic, saut√©ing until translucent.
Add the beef stew meat to the pot, browning it on all sides.
Stir in the carrots, potatoes, and celery, mixing well with the beef.
Pour in the beef broth and add the tomato paste, bay leaf, thyme, salt, and pepper. Stir to combine.
Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for about 45 minutes, or until the beef is tender and the vegetables are cooked through.
While the stew is simmering, cook the rice according to package instructions.
Once the stew is ready, remove the bay leaf and serve hot over a bed of rice.
data.detailedName: Hearty Beef and Vegetable Stew with Fluffy Rice
